   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
        
		
		  <div n="i" type="textpart" subtype="section"><ab><lb n="1"/><persName key="Symbaticius" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Συμβατίκιος"><expan><abbr><am><g ref="#monogram"/></am></abbr><ex>Συμβατικίου</ex></expan></name></persName></ab></div>
		
		  <div n="ii" type="textpart" subtype="section"><ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Συμβατίκιος"><expan><abbr><am><g ref="#monogram"/></am></abbr><ex>Συμβατικίου</ex></expan></name></persName></ab></div>
		
		  <div n="iii" type="textpart" subtype="section"><ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Συμβατίκιος"><expan><abbr><am><g ref="#monogram"/></am></abbr><ex>Συμβατικίου</ex></expan></name></persName></ab></div>
		
		  <div n="iv" type="textpart" subtype="section"><ab>
		 <lb n="1"/> <persName key="Michael" type="divine"><persName key="michael6" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μιχαήλ"><expan><abbr>Μ</abbr><ex>ι</ex><abbr>χ</abbr><ex>αήλ</ex></expan></name></persName></persName>
		 <lb n="2"/><g ref="#cross"/></ab></div>
      </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>In the first edition it was implied that all four capitals were identical; in fact the fourth does not have the same monogram as the other three.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>i-iii. John Nesbitt suggested, on the basis of the photographs, the resolution <persName full="yes">
                  <foreign xml:lang="grc">Συμβατικίου</foreign>
               </persName>, 'of <persName full="yes">Symbaticius</persName>'.</p>
            <p>iv. MX, perhaps for <persName full="yes">Michael</persName>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="VII.17" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p>An inferior account published by <bibl>
                  <author>Roueché</author>, <title level="m">Aphrodisias in Late Antiquity</title> no. <citedRange>101</citedRange> and plate xxvii</bibl>, whence <bibl>
                  <title level="m">PHI</title>
                  <citedRange>614-7</citedRange>
               </bibl>.</p>
